feeling about this, but if you're planning to go to the
ruins ahead, I'd advise against it.

\N<Man>The entrance management of the ruins that have been in this
town for ages is now being handled by Luda's soldiers...

\N<Man>Even the entrance management of the ruins that have been in

\N<Man>There are still those in the city who attempt to resist the

\N<Fubii>Hey, ma'am. Tomorrow's the day of the battle at the training
grounds, right? How's it going? Are you prepared?

\N<Fubii>That's not true. You haven't forgotten, have you? I was your
opponent too. That means I have a claim on you as well.
\N<Segi>Claim... Stop talking about people as if they're objects.

\N<Fubii>Ahaha, but it's true. The right to own you... even at this
very moment.
\N<Segi>W-wait... n-not here...! What if someone sees us...!?

\N<Fubii>Then let's go somewhere out of sight. That would be okay,
right?

\N<Fubii>Hehe, you've become quite aggressive. Desperately moving
your hips like that. Is it the effect of that drug, I
wonder?

\N<Segi>It's not like that...! You're the one who... forcefully
brought me here...!

\N<Fubii>But you wouldn't do this with your husband in such a place,
right?

\N<Fubii>So, you've become more aggressive after all. At least
towards me. I'm happy about that.

\N<Segi>Don't get so pleased with yourself... hurry up and
finish...!

\N<Voice Of The Residents>Those two looked suspicious no matter how you slice it...
They must be around here somewhere.

\N<Voice Of The Residents>That might be true, but even if we find them, what are we
going to do?

\N<Voice Of The Residents>It's obvious, isn't it? We'll warn them. They could be
causing a disturbance to public morals, right?

\N<Fubii>Hehe, did you hear that? What a masterpiece, it's a lie
though.

\N<Fubii>They're planning to blackmail us if they find us. No doubt
about it. Talking about disturbing public morals, it's
laughable.

\N<Fubii>Yeah, their goal is your body. If I can have you, they think
they should too. Men's thoughts are always the same no
matter their age.

\N<Fubii>You wouldn't want that, right? So we have to make sure we're
not found. Be quiet, okay?

\N<Fubii>Well, just waiting for those people to leave is boring. A
little bit of fun is fine, right?
\N<Segi>Stop... Do you realize the situation we're in...!

\N<Fubii>Hey, ma'am. There's something I want to try out, is that
okay with you?
\N<Segi>What are you saying... stop... wait a minute...!

\N<Fubii>It's fine, you just have to keep your voice down. So, can
you bear with it for a little while...?
\N<Fubii>Ahaha, just as I thought. You're making such a nice face?

\N<Fubii>Ma'am, you're really weak when it comes to being teased,
aren't you? You were trying so hard to bluff the first time
we did it, right?

\N<Fubii>Right? When I tried to do it, you panicked and said you
wanted to be on top?

\N<Fubii>So? That means you knew that if I teased you like this,
you'd fall easily, didn't you?
\N<Segi>That's not... such a thing...! Stop... we'll be found...!

\N<Fubii>But now, there's no need to hide your little secret anymore,
right? At least not from me.

\N<Fubii>Ahaha, then try to keep your voice down a bit. I understand
it feels good to have your weak spots teased.

\N<Fubii>Come on, do your best. It would be trouble if they found us,
right?

\N<Fubii>It would be trouble, wouldn't it? I wonder what kind of face
your husband and Riia would make if they knew you were doing
this with me here?

\N<Fubii>So we have to keep it a secret. Now's the time to really try
hard, right?

\N<Segi>You too... might not get off scot-free... yet despite
that... what are you planning...?

\N<Fubii>Hmm, that's true. But if we get caught, that might be
interesting in its own way. Sorry for surprising you all of
a sudden.

\N<Segi>No...ah... if something like that happens... we won't be
able to live in this town anymore...
\N<Fubii>Don't cry. We'll really get found out, you know?
\N<Voice Of The Residents>How about it... were they there?

\N<Voice Of The Residents>No, they weren't over there either. They might be hiding
somewhere...
\N<Voice Of The Residents>I see... it's getting late. Let's give up for today.

\N<Voice Of The Residents>Yeah, that's right, it's a shame. If we had caught them in
the act, we could have had all sorts of fun.
\N<Voice Of The Residents>Don't worry, there will be another chance.
\N<Fubii>Have they gone...? Auntie, are you okay now?
\N<Segi>Why... why would you... do something like this...

\N<Fubii>Because I thought this was the best way. You were crying,
and I thought it'd be better to cover your mouth before we
got found.

\N<Fubii>Did you not like it? Or were you just surprised? Sorry for
saying it seemed fun, okay?
\N<Segi>...I have to go pick up Riia.
\N<Segi>...I have to go pick up Riia.

\N<Segi>Actually, I saw the request board at the management
office... Rozaro-san's.

\N<Rozaro>Request board? Ah, you mean the sparring partner thing. What
about it?
\N<Segi>...Well, I was wondering if I might be of any help to you?

\N<Segi>Yes, I am aware that I might not be strong enough to be your
sparring partner.

\N<Segi>But you have always been a great help to both my son and me,
and more than anything, it would serve as good training for
myself as well.

\N<Segi>I know it's selfish of me to offer to help with your
training when in reality it's for my own benefit.
\N<Segi>But... what do you think? Could I be of any help to you?

\N<Rozaro>...Understood. Then I'll accept your offer without
reservation.
\N<Segi>Really? Thank you so much. I'll do my very best.

\N<Rozaro>Of course, I'll pay you for your time as a training partner.
But since it's training, I can't hold back. Is that alright
with you?

\N<Rozaro>Hmm, then let's begin in the forest outskirts as soon as
you're ready.
\N<Rozaro>Then, Segi-san, shall we start the training right away?

\N<Rozaro>...Segi-san, don't overdo it. You should rest a bit. You're
not ready to spar with me just yet.
\N<Segi>No, I'm fine... What should I... help with next...

\N<Rozaro>...I appreciate the sentiment. But if we've managed to find
this time, I want it to be meaningful for you too.

\N<Rozaro>In other words... I want this training to be beneficial for
you as well, not just for me.

\N<Rozaro>That's why from here on out, let's focus on training for
your sake. Consider it part of my request to you, is that
okay?

\N<Rozaro>Don't thank me just yet. Of course, I'll take it seriously
since I'm involved. Make sure you don't regret agreeing to
train with me.

\N<Rozaro>Hmm... Listen, Segi-san. As a warrior who must fight, there
are several key elements you're critically lacking.

\N<Rozaro>One is muscular strength, the source of power for attacks.
Another is stamina, essential for defense against attacks.
And one more is vitality, the essence of life.

\N<Rozaro>All are important elements in battle. Now, what do you
consider important? I'll accompany you in any training you
wish to focus on.

\N<Segi>(Indeed, all the elements Rozaro-san mentioned seem
important... Which one should I choose...)

\N<Rozaro>You're focusing on muscular strength. Understood. Then let's
proceed with today's training in that manner.

\N<Rozaro>Ah, it was good training for me too. Plus, I plan to keep
posting requests on the management office board regularly
from now on.

\N<Rozaro>If you feel like it, please call on me again. I'm always
ready to assist you.
